### 1. `Extensions/ArmClientBuilderExtensions.cs` (line 30 - IL2026/IL3050)
The method `AddArmClient<TBuilder, TConfiguration>` calls `builder.RegisterClientFactory` which has `[RequiresUnreferencedCode]` and `[RequiresDynamicCode]`. Add `[RequiresUnreferencedCode]` and `[RequiresDynamicCode]` attributes to the method. The file already imports `System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis`.

Add these attributes to the `AddArmClient<TBuilder, TConfiguration>` method:
```csharp
[RequiresUnreferencedCode("Binding strongly typed objects to configuration values is not supported with trimming. Use the Configuration Binder Source Generator (EnableConfigurationBindingGenerator=true) instead.")]
[RequiresDynamicCode("Binding strongly typed objects to configuration values requires generating dynamic code at runtime, for example instantiating generic types. Use the Configuration Binder Source Generator (EnableConfigurationBindingGenerator=true) instead.")]
```

### 2. `GenericOperationSource.cs` (lines 37, 40 - IL2087)
The class `GenericOperationSource<T>` uses:
- `ModelReaderWriter.Read(response.Content, typeof(T))` (line 37) - which requires `PublicConstructors | NonPublicConstructors` on the type
- `Activator.CreateInstance(typeof(T), ...)` with `BindingFlags.NonPublic | BindingFlags.Instance` (line 40) - which requires `NonPublicConstructors`

Add `[DynamicallyAccessedMembers]` to the generic type parameter `T` on the class declaration:
```csharp
internal class GenericOperationSource<[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.PublicConstructors | DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)] T> : IOperationSource<T>
```

### 3. `ArmOperation.cs` (lines 98, 104 - IL2087/IL2090)
The `IsResource<T>()` method uses:
- `typeof(T).GetConstructor(BindingFlags.NonPublic | BindingFlags.Instance, ...)` (line 98) - requires `NonPublicConstructors`
- `Activator.CreateInstance(typeof(T), BindingFlags.NonPublic | BindingFlags.Instance, ...)` (line 104) - requires `NonPublicConstructors`

Add `[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)]` to the `T` type parameter on `IsResource<T>()`:
```csharp
private static bool IsResource<[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)] T>() where T : notnull
```

Also need to add `using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;` to ArmOperation.cs since it doesn't have it yet.

Then cascade the annotation to the callers of `IsResource<T>()`:

`Rehydrate<T>` (line 44): Add `[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.PublicConstructors | DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)]` to its `T` - it needs both `PublicConstructors | NonPublicConstructors` because it also creates `GenericOperationSource<T>` which requires that. The method signature becomes:
```csharp
public static ArmOperation<T> Rehydrate<[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.PublicConstructors | DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)] T>(ArmClient client, RehydrationToken rehydrationToken, ArmClientOptions options = null) where T : notnull
```

`RehydrateAsync<T>` (line 82): Same annotation:
```csharp
public static async Task<ArmOperation<T>> RehydrateAsync<[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.PublicConstructors | DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)] T>(ArmClient client, RehydrationToken rehydrationToken, ArmClientOptions options = null) where T : notnull
```

### 4. `ArmEnvironment.cs` (line 80 - IL2026/IL3050)
`JsonSerializer.Serialize(this)` in `ToString()` method. Replace with a source-gen-safe approach. Since `ArmEnvironment` is a simple struct with `Endpoint` (Uri) and `Audience` (string), just build a JSON string manually:

Replace:
```csharp
public override string ToString() => JsonSerializer.Serialize(this);
```
With:
```csharp
public override string ToString()
{
    return $"{{\"Endpoint\":\"{Endpoint}\",\"Audience\":\"{Audience}\",\"DefaultScope\":\"{DefaultScope}\"}}";
}
```

Wait, that could have escaping issues. Better to use `Utf8JsonWriter`:
```csharp
public override string ToString()
{
    var buffer = new System.Buffers.ArrayBufferWriter<byte>();
    using (var writer = new Utf8JsonWriter(buffer))
    {
        writer.WriteStartObject();
        writer.WriteString("Endpoint", Endpoint?.ToString());
        writer.WriteString("Audience", Audience);
        writer.WriteString("DefaultScope", DefaultScope);
        writer.WriteEndObject();
    }
    return System.Text.Encoding.UTF8.GetString(buffer.WrittenSpan);
}
```

Add `using System.Buffers;` and `using System.Text;` if not already present. Actually check first what usings are already there.

### 5. `ArmClientOptions.cs` (line 52 - IL2026/IL3050)
`JsonSerializer.Deserialize<Dictionary<string, Dictionary<string, JsonElement>>>(span)` - Replace by parsing manually with `JsonDocument`:

Replace:
```csharp
var allProfile = JsonSerializer.Deserialize<Dictionary<string, Dictionary<string, JsonElement>>>(span);
```
With manual parsing using JsonDocument (which is AOT-safe):
```csharp
using var doc = JsonDocument.Parse(BinaryData.FromStream(stream));
```
Then iterate `doc.RootElement` to get the same data. Wait, looking at the code more carefully (lines 48-78 of ArmClientOptions.cs):

```csharp
